verbs.description: The election of Donald Trump [V: has] proven something I 've suspected for many years -- there is little difference between Washington politics and professional wrestling . There are donkeys and elephants ( good start for a zoo ) , but behind closed doors there are only skunks . Trump won the election by a substantial electoral margin yet all Democrats and many Republicans refuse to support him because they want him gone . Too bad , he 's here . Trump and a large percentage of Americans want the wall built , border laws enforced and sanctuary cities eliminated , yet nothing gets done . Republicans need to supply their large corporate campaign donors with cheap labor and Democrats need to prop up their voter base for future elections because they are virtually dead in the water . Democrats rode the wave of Harry Reid , Nancy Pelosi and other aging dinosaurs to extinction and have no new blood or creative ideas for upcoming elections . The only platform they will present is " hate Trump . " Democrats and the media try their best to hide the fact that Trump 's approval rating is inching upward , but it is . Why ? Because he is doing something few politicians ever do , deliver on campaign promises . His statistical successes are remarkable ...
